<h3 id="dynamics">Dynamics</h3>

<h4 id="compressor">Compressor</h4>

<img src="/assets/BlueCat/Axiom/Effects/Dynamics/Compressor.png" alt="Compressor">
<div class="image-caption">Compressor</div>

<p>I haven‚Äôt dived in deep with this thing, but it‚Äôs surprisingly nice. I‚Äôve tried it solo on bass guitar and on drums, and it‚Äôs quite good for soft compression.</p>

<p>It does an excellent job in effects chains of doing light, barely audible compression. The type of compression that‚Äôs often necessary to keep certain bits under control.</p>

<h4 id="destructor-2">Destructor</h4>

<img src="/assets/BlueCat/Axiom/Destructor.png" alt="Destructor">
<div class="image-caption">Destructor</div>

<p><a href="#destructor">Already covered.</a></p>

<h4 id="ducker">Ducker</h4>

<img src="/assets/BlueCat/Axiom/Effects/Dynamics/Ducker.png" alt="Ducker">
<div class="image-caption">Ducker</div>

<h4 id="gate">Gate</h4>

<img src="/assets/BlueCat/Axiom/Effects/Dynamics/Gate.png" alt="Gate">
<div class="image-caption">Gate</div>

<p>This gate is damn near useless. It has no hysteresis at all, which is a feature that allows the gate to close at a different level than it opens. There is also no hold, and the release shape seems aggressive.</p>

<p>The result is that you get a chattery, sensitive gate that is difficult to use for anything musical.</p>

<p>It is possible to use it on sources that are clearly ‚Äòon‚Äô or ‚Äòoff‚Äô, like metal guitars, but even then I rather use another product since this is still finicky to tune.</p>

<h3 id="eq-and-filters">EQ and Filters</h3>

<h4 id="comb-filter">Comb Filter</h4>

<img src="/assets/BlueCat/Axiom/Effects/Filters/CombFilter.png" alt="CombFilter">
<div class="image-caption">CombFilter</div>

<h4 id="comb-filter-iir">Comb Filter IIR</h4>

<img src="/assets/BlueCat/Axiom/Effects/Filters/CombFilterIIR.png" alt="CombFilterIIR">
<div class="image-caption">CombFilterIIR</div>

<p>Rather than implementing a combfilter as a simple delay + mix, this implements it as an <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infinite_impulse_response">IIR filter</a>. Sometimes this is a more appropriate selection compared to <a href="#comb-filter">Comb Filter</a> due to the phase rotation that occurs. Often more appropriate in delay lines, but the sky is the limit.</p>

<h4 id="eq">EQ</h4>

<img src="/assets/BlueCat/Axiom/Effects/Filters/EQ.png" alt="EQ">
<div class="image-caption">EQ</div>

<p>This EQ is similar to the <a href="#preamp">Preamp EQ in Destructor</a>. It has the same spectrogram capabilities, same <a href="https://www.bluecataudio.com/Tutorials/Tutorial_EQ_Matching_Reaper/">reference curve functionality</a>. It‚Äôs missing the comb filter, and that‚Äôs it.</p>

<p>It‚Äôs a better EQ than some DAWs come with. (I‚Äôm looking at you <a href="/tags/#Tracktion+Waveform">Waveform</a>!)</p>

<h4 id="filter">Filter</h4>

<img src="/assets/BlueCat/Axiom/Effects/Filters/Filter.png" alt="Filter">
<div class="image-caption">Filter</div>

<p>What a wimpy filter. BLERGH.</p>

<p>It‚Äôs lucky that you can use 3rd party VST/VST3/AU plugins or I‚Äôd be throwing a tantrum that‚Äôd put any 2-year old to shame. I like my filter plugins, and this is a wussy filter.</p>

<h4 id="wah">Wah</h4>

<img src="/assets/BlueCat/Axiom/Effects/Filters/Wah.png" alt="Wah">
<div class="image-caption">Wah</div>

<p>This is one of the standout effects. It‚Äôs an <em>excellent</em> wah pedal. It‚Äôs MIDI assignable to an expression pedal of course, and there‚Äôs an auto-wah section that allows the wah to respond automatically to input dynamics.</p>

<p>The wah allows you to select the low and high positions for the wah movement. The bandwidth and gain are also selectable. You can get rather creative with it and make some mindwarping sounds in conjunction with other effects.</p>

<h3 id="fx">FX</h3>

<h4 id="bit-crusher">Bit Crusher</h4>

<img src="/assets/BlueCat/Axiom/Effects/FX/BitCrusher.png" alt="BitCrusher">
<div class="image-caption">BitCrusher</div>

<p>Thank you Blue Cat for having a bit crusher/decimator that has <em>variable antialiasing</em>. Sometimes you want only a bit of grit and darkes, not a nails on the chalkboard sound.</p>

<p>Old hardware designers weren‚Äôt stupid, and when you want to try to emulate old devices it‚Äôs sometimes necessary to have mild anti-aliasing. Bit Crusher provides it.</p>

<h4 id="freq-shifter">Freq Shifter</h4>

<img src="/assets/BlueCat/Axiom/Effects/FX/FreqShifter.png" alt="FreqShifter">
<div class="image-caption">FreqShifter</div>

<p>If you don‚Äôt know how a frequency shifter differs from a pitch shifter: <a href="/music/2017/06/27/Bitwig-Effects-review.html#freq-shifter">I explained it here</a></p>

<h4 id="harmonizer">Harmonizer</h4>

<img src="/assets/BlueCat/Axiom/Effects/FX/Harmonizer.png" alt="Harmonizer">
<div class="image-caption">Harmonizer</div>

<p>I have one thing to say about Harmonizer: no PDC.</p>

<p>To get a decent sound, Harmonizer requires a lookahead. The larger the lookahead, the cleaner the sound. Obviously we can‚Äôt have realtime lookahead, since time travel doesn‚Äôt exist yet. So when playing live you get this echoed pitch shifted signal happening. It is what it is.</p>

<p>The issue comes up when you want to use Axiom on a recording. I would like that delay compensated, ideally variably compensated. This effect would be far more useful with this capability.</p>

<p>Strangely enough, Axiom does report latency for VST/AUs properly. It‚Äôs a bit weird that it‚Äôs unable to let you offset detection latency on Harmonizer.</p>

<h4 id="phase-shifter">Phase Shifter</h4>

<img src="/assets/BlueCat/Axiom/Effects/FX/PhaseShifter.png" alt="PhaseShifter">
<div class="image-caption">PhaseShifter</div>

<p>Phase shifter may seem somewhat useless, but herein lies the utility of kings. When working with dense modulation/delay/reverb effects or parallel effect chains, there‚Äôs often times where you get nasty frequency cancellations.</p>

<p>Phase shifter lets you target an area and rotate the phase. Problem solved</p>

<p>Of course this can be used prophylactically when creating reverb like effects.</p>

<h4 id="pitch-bender">Pitch Bender</h4>

<img src="/assets/BlueCat/Axiom/Effects/FX/PitchBender.png" alt="PitchBender">
<div class="image-caption">PitchBender</div>

<p><a href="#harmonizer">See Harmonizer</a> for why I dislike this effect.</p>

<h4 id="pitch-shifter">Pitch Shifter</h4>

<img src="/assets/BlueCat/Axiom/Effects/FX/PitchShifter.png" alt="PitchShifter">
<div class="image-caption">PitchShifter</div>

<h4 id="waveshaper-1">Waveshaper</h4>

<img src="/assets/BlueCat/Axiom/Effects/Distortion/WaveShaper.png" alt="Waveshaper">
<div class="image-caption">WaveShaper</div>

<h3 id="modulation">Modulation</h3>

<h4 id="chorus">Chorus</h4>

<img src="/assets/BlueCat/Axiom/Effects/Modulation/Chorus.png" alt="Chorus">
<div class="image-caption">Chorus</div>

